race.comment: Happy to stick with KINGSWOOD (1) off a tough win at Flemington in the Listed Cup Day Plate over this distance, third up there and proving too strong late for a handy field. He's a talented horse who has found his right sort of level and range, and with a repeat performance he looks the one to beat. Not knocking the stablemate CASINO SEVENTEEN (2). He needs another win but his past two have been good - third in the G3 Coongy with 59kg then a decent fifth in a fast run G3 JRA Cup. He can figure with luck from the inside gate. POISON CHALICE (5) is ready to win. Two runs back have been good, closing off strongly behind Apulia at Flemington last start over 1600m. On his day he's certainly got the ability to win this. DETONATOR JACK (3) was much better last time through the Apulia race too. He hasn't won in a long time but should be right there again. RUMBLED AGAIN (6) was a shock winner last time and gets in well but this is harder.
